Nigerian online marketplace, Jaraa.com, is set to launch full operations on the 1st of April, 2022. Jaraa.com is a one-stop destination for selling or buying almost anything online, without the usual worries. It comes with top of the line security systems, providing a safe and hassle free environment for trade of goods and services anywhere in Nigeria. Beyond being a digital marketplace for buying and selling almost anything, Jaraa operates with a special bias for Nigerian SMEs, designing its operations to engage and provide support for entrepreneurs selling on its platform, helping them sell more, access more information, improve capacity, and grow their businesses faster. Speaking on how Jaraa is set to transform the marketplace landscape through its innovative platform, Jaraa’s Head of Marketing, Modupe Sanni, said, the platform is set to redefine the culture of digital buying and selling, improving user experience and enabling smoother transactions between buyers and sellers, while supporting SMEs to thrive, sell more and grow sustainably.  She said: “Jaraa is a Nigerian digital marketplace with global intentions starting from home. We believe the e-commerce ecosystem, especially in Nigeria, can do more, and make improvements in the user experience journey. That’s what we are about – making digital buying and selling a much easier engagement for both buyers and sellers. “While at it, we make sure to keep important focus on a most critical agenda: to support SMEs on the platform, by helping them grow their businesses through better sales and improved capacity,” she added. The Jaraa app is ready for download on both the Apple store and Google Play store.